                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of March 19. Colombian minister for foreign affairs says that he
                    believes when the assembly approves the treaty with Panama it will adopt a
                    resolution declaring that “Region of Jurado” does not extend south of Jurado
                    River. He says such a resolution would enormously facilitate Government’s labors
                    to secure approval. Desires your opinion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
